    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-04-21T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-04-21T23:00:00-05:00" n="12"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d12">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">756.94/49: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-04-22T13:00:00+09:00"
                            >April 22, 1940—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 22—1:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>273. Our 269, April 20, 5 p.m.<note n="30" xml:id="d12fn30">Not printed.</note>
                    This morning’s vernacular press reports that, after an interview with the
                    Secretary of State on April 20, Ambassador Horinouchi announced that Japan and
                    the United States have reached an agreement in principle with regard to the
                    question of the maintenance of the <hi rend="italic">status quo</hi> of the
                    Dutch East Indies.<note n="31" xml:id="d12fn31">See memorandum by the Secretary
                        of State, April 20, <ref target="frus1931-41v02#pg_283">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 283</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
